703629f-b.text:
Clermont Avenue, east side, between Myrtle and Willoughby Avenues, viewing south from the former and showing the 52nd Field Artillery Armory, also known as
the 105th Regiment Field Armory.
View 2 shows the rear of the armory on the west side of Vanderbilt Avenue, looking toward Myrtle Avenue. View 3 shows another front view, with the extreme
right portion of the armory gone.
Views 1,2: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection October, 1925
View 3: P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS  October 12, 1940
1:3 E19 View : NEG RR23S
Dg  14S U;3 We: 2N.EG 520
